display_name: ID -participants id that is specific to this study.
description: IDs are 6 digits; however, participants who participated in a previous study in the lab will have an 8-digit ID: 2 digits following their 6-digit study id to indicate previous lab study participation and how many studies [02 at end is one previous study; 03 is two, etc.]

display_name: season - season at time of dems data collection; calculated using defined dates for start and end of each season in each year of study
season_demsfile -variable in original demographics file defining season
Session -study session; refers to timepoint of data collection.
Year_Study -year of study participation. Enrollment began in 2002; every 6 mos follow up continued until last one in 2007.
comments_PEForm -study team comments re tanner staging assessment recorded on physical exam form
height_physexam - ppts height as recorded on physical exam form during tanner assessment
tannero - assessed tanner stage, other characteristics
tannerph - assessed tanner stage, pubic hair
weight_physexam - ppts weight as recorded on physical exam form during tanner assessment
bdi1 -beck depression inventory item 1 sadness
bdi10 -beck depression inventory item 10 crying
bdi11 -beck depression inventory item 11 agitation
bdi12 -beck depression inventory item 12 loss of interest
bdi13 -beck depression inventory item 13 indecisiveness
bdi14 -beck depression inventory item 14 worthlessness
bdi15 -beck depression inventory item 15 loss of energy
bdi16 -beck depression inventory item 16 changes in sleeping pattern
bdi17 -beck depression inventory item 17 irritability
bdi18 -beck depression inventory item 18 changes in appetite
bdi19 -beck depression inventory item 19 concentration difficulty
bdi2 -beck depression inventory item 2 pessimism
bdi20 -beck depression inventory item 20 tiredness or fatigue
bdi3 -beck depression inventory item 3 past failure
bdi4 -beck depression inventory item 4 loss of pleasure
bdi5 -beck depression inventory item 5 sadness
bdi6 -beck depression inventory item 6 punishment feelings
bdi7 -beck depression inventory item 7 self-dislike
bdi8 -beck depression inventory item 8 self-criticalness
bdi9 -beck depression inventory item 9 suicidal thoughts or wishes

bdi_score - all 20 items must have response [this modified BDI omitted item 21 as not appropriate for population). Score is mean of all 1-20 items w response, multiplied by 21 [# of items in full BDI]. Possible range: 0-63

bdi_score$ - missing items allowed [14/20 items required; this modified BDI omitted item 21;not appropriate for population]. Score is mean of 14 out of 20 items with response, multiplied by 21 [#of items in full BDI]. range: 0-63

display_name: Rutter_TOTAL - sum of all responses to rutter items 1 through 24.
adisf -result of adis for father.
adism -result of adis for mother.
FamHx_ETOH_status --variable to specify either the absence of etoh disorder in the parents, or if present, in which parent or both.
FamHx_ETOH_yn -variable to identify presence or absence of any parent with a history of an etoh disorder [abuse or dependence].
accx -Acceleration index (change in activity rate during interval)
day_sequence - variable to identify order/sequence of actigraphy days for each participant.
description: 1 is first day of recorded actigraphy, then numbers are continuous for the full time frame of their participation in the study. Variable to identify sequence in the absence of date information. Can be used to sort file in order of date of data collection in lieu of having date variable in file. NOTE: final number indicates total number of days of actigraphy data for each participant.

display_name: Year_Study -year of study participation
actx -Activity index (percent of epochs with an activity score greater than 0)
amean -Activity Mean -Average activity score
amed -Activity Median - Median activity score
asd -Activity SD - Standard deviation of activity mean
bad -Bad Epochs - Total epochs marked as bad
bwr -Brief wake ratio: Brief Wakes (duration of 1 min or less) /√ä Number of Awakenings (Wake Episodes)

days_betweensessionstartdates -variable to identify span of days from start of this sessions actigraphy days to the start of the previous sessions [startdate this session minus startdate of previous session]

days_numbersincesessiononestart -variable to identify number of days this row of actigraphy data is from the very first day of actigraphy at baseline [date of this row of actigraphy minus date of very first day of actigraphy at baseline]
dur -Duration - minutes from start to end of Interval
eday -End Day - End of sleep interval - day of the week
etime -End Time - End of sleep interval - time
IntName -Interval Type - Custom intervals
lgsep -Longest sleep episode -Duration of longest sleep episode
lgwep -Longest Wake Episode - Duration of longest wake episode
lsep -Long sleep episodes - Number of Sleep Episodes >= duration in Options: Sleep: Sleep Statistics Criteria text box
lwep -Long wake episodes (wake episodes greater than or equal to 5 min [value specified in W2 program Options:Sleep:Sleep Statistics Criteria])
mid -Midpoint - Midpoint time of interval
msep -Mean Sleep Episode - Mean duration of sleep episodes
mwep -Mean Wake Episode - Mean duration of wake episodes
pslp -Percent Sleep - Percent minutes during the interval scored as sleep (100 * Sleep/Duration)
sbix -Short burst inactivity index (zero activity of 1 min duration/zero activity of any duration)
sday -Start Day - Start of sleep interval - day of the week
sday_actig -from scored actigraphy data file: Start Day of actigraphy collection for this session; day of the week
season_precise - season/time of year on this day of this session of actigraphy; based precisely on the dates defining that season in that year
Season_SessionStart - season/time of year on the first day of this session of actigraphy; season may change during the session depending on the dates defining that season in that year
seff -Sleep efficiency (100 * Sleep minutes/Duration)
sep -Sleep Episodes - Number of sleep episodes (blocks of contiguous sleep epochs)
sfx -Sleep fragmentation index (number of awakenings/total sleep time [mins] * 100)
slat -sleep onset latency
smin -Sleep Minutes -Total minutes scored as sleep during the interval
stime -Start Time -Start of sleep interval - time
waso -Wake After Sleep Onset - Wake min during O-O interval
wep -Wake Episodes - Number of wake episodes (blocks of contiguous wake epochs)
wmin -Wake Minutes - Total minutes scored as wake during the interval
DLMO -assessed dim light melatonin onset via saliva samples collected serially and then assayed for melatonin values [threshold = 4pg/ml] in decimalized clocktime

smith1 - Considering only your own “feeling best” rhythm, at what time would you get up if you were entirely free to plan your day?

smith13r -smith item 13 -morning or evening individual- reverse coded per scoring key/algorithm for scoring smith

smith2 -Considering only your own √ífeeling best√ì rhythm, at what time would you go to bed if you were entirely free to plan your evening?

SMITH_ME_Type -ppts chronotype based on their SMITH total$ score.
SMITH_TOT -Smith total score. items 1,2,6,7,8,9,10,12,13 reverse coded; all 13 items required. range 13 to 55
SMITH_TOT$ -Smith total score. items 1,2,6,7,8,9,10,12,13 reverse coded; 9 out of 13 items required. range 13 to 55
SHS_PDS_score -SHS_PDS_score -pubertal development scale score per original measure directions: mean of all items. Range: 1-4. All items must be present to get score
SHS_PDS_score$ -SHS_PDS_score$ -pubertal development scale score per original measure directions: mean of all items, allowing for missing items. Range: 1-4. 4 of 5 items must be present to get score
SHS_Pubertal_Category -pubertal category using items from the pubertal development scale.  Range1-5. All items must be present to get score
SHS_Pubertal_Category$ -pubertal category using items from the pubertal development scale [SHS_Pubertal_Category_Sum$].  Range1-5. for girls menarche data must be present to get score
